description._content: Description: Albert Street (part of), Victoria, showing Chausee widened in 1902 by average of 6 feet, and new parapet side wall 2 1/2 feet high. Depth from level of roadway 5 feet. Total length 1,029. Width of present road 26 feet. Location: Victoria, Seychelles Date: 1890-1909 Description: Panoramic view of Victoria, Capital of Mahe. The Islands in the distance reading from left to right, are Moyenne (property of Miss E.W. Best), Round (Mr Baty), Long (Government Quarantine Station), and Stag (belonging to Calais family). Location: Victoria, Seychelles Date: 1890-1909 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/770 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives.
